hands_on_practices.solution:
1. The scalar part of a rank-2 tensor is proportional to its trace: 
   $$S^{\mu\nu}\propto g^{\mu\nu}T^\rho{}_\rho
    =g^{\mu\nu}g_{\alpha\beta}T^{\alpha\beta}\,. $$
2. Define 
   $$(P^{(0)})^{\mu\nu}{}_{\alpha\beta}
     =C\,g^{\mu\nu}g_{\alpha\beta}\,, $$
   so that 
   $$S^{\mu\nu}=(P^{(0)})^{\mu\nu}{}_{\alpha\beta}T^{\alpha\beta}
    =C\,g^{\mu\nu}g_{\alpha\beta}T^{\alpha\beta}\,. $$
3. Imposing idempotency,
   $$(P^{(0)})^{\mu\nu}{}_{\sigma\rho}
     (P^{(0)})^{\sigma\rho}{}_{\alpha\beta}
    =C^2\,g^{\mu\nu}g_{\sigma\rho}g^{\sigma\rho}g_{\alpha\beta}
    =4C^2\,g^{\mu\nu}g_{\alpha\beta}
    \stackrel!=C\,g^{\mu\nu}g_{\alpha\beta}\,. $$
4. Thus $4C^2=C\implies C=\frac{1}{4}\,$.
5. Hence
   $$(P^{(0)})^{\mu\nu}{}_{\alpha\beta}
    =\frac{1}{4}\,g^{\mu\nu}g_{\alpha\beta}\,. $$
